        <p>Yugoslav Fighting Worsens</p>
        <p>Yugoslav Army and Serbian rebel forces pounded towns in the secessionist republic of Croatia for hours in the heaviest fighting yet. page A3.</p>
        <p>U.N. Optimism on Hostages</p>
        <p>After discussing the hostage issue with a chief aide, the United Nations Secretary General said "we are moving at a good pace." Page A3. Cuts in Medicare Restored</p>
        <p>Federal health officials said they would restore $6.9 billion that was to have been cut from Medicare payment to doctors. The change was a response to Congressional pressure and doctors' complaints. Page A19.</p>
